Package: kro.inv.test
Title: Kronecker-Invariant Tests for High-Dimensional Separability Testing
Version: 0.1.0
Description: Kronecker-invariant tests for high-dimensional separability testing of matrix-variate data.Tests whether the population covariance matrix is represented as a Kronecker product of row and column covariance matrices. Provides the tests whose test statistics are invariant to the separable component of the population covariance matrix, referred to as Kronecker-invariance, based on the sample core. Tests constructed based on the largest eigenvalue, the extended LRT for sphericity testing, and the separable expansion of the sample core. For details, see Sung and Hoff (2025) <https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2506.17463>.
